This paper deals with the self-adjustment of parameters in evolutionary algorithms, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm on linear functions and MAX-SAT instances, which are problems commonly studied in the field of optimization and algorithms (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a modification to the one fifth rule, which is a technique used in evolutionary algorithms, and discusses its theoretical and practical performance, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents experimental results, which can be considered as computational engineering (cs.CE).
